title: Per capita consumption of high fructose corn syrup in the U.S. 2000 to 2018
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Per capita consumption in pounds, containing a total of 19 data points.
In general Per capita consumption in pounds has fallen over the Year.
Per capita consumption in pounds is roughly constant from 2000 to 2005, gradually decreasing from 2005 to 2013, roughly constant from 2013 to 2014, and lastly slightly decreasing from 2014 to 2018.
The steepest decrease occurs in between the Year 2007 and 2008.
The highest Per capita consumption in pounds, of value 62.5 was reached at Year 2000, and 2002
Minimum Per capita consumption in pounds about 37.6 was reached at Year 2018
